<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-03-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-03-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="264" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d264">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-03-09"><hi rend="italic">March 9,
                            1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>We have trustworthy information that a few days since a British military
                        force landed at Bluefields in the Mosquito territory. You are instructed to
                        ascertain and report fully by cable the occasion for this action.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>